        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-02 22:07:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nMy reading of this code is that it creates a new node type (clamp.nodes.policy) derived from dcae.nodes.policy.  The new type adds a property to the node.  It also *replaces* the dcae.nodes.policy implementation of the \"create\" operation with a dummy operation that does nothing.  This means that putting a component in a blueprint and linking via a relationship to a clamp.nodes.policy node will *not* provide the component with any configuration information from policy.  Is this what's intended?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
